Business Brief -- Bristol-Myers Squibb Co.:
   Increase of 20% in Earnings
   Is Posted for 4th Quarter
For the year, net rose to $2.06 billion, or $3.95 a share,
from $1.75 billion, or $3.33 a share, in 1990. Sales rose to
$11.16 billion from $10.3 billion.
   The company said that in the year domestic sales rose 10%
and international sales climbed 6%. All business groups
showed gains except consumer products, which were flat.
Pharmaceutical sales rose 12%, medical-devices sales were up
15% and nutritional sales rose 9%.
   Bristol-Myers shares fell 75 cents yesterday to $83.75 in
late trading on the New York Stock Exchange.